	   <tr><td colspan=2>My counter question is: Why are you casting ward undead? You could almost certainly do more damage at level 22 by meleeing, given cast time, possible interuption, and resists. If you cannot and play on MT, I have an axe of the iron back rotting in the bank you can have for free so you can. Unless there is a level 50+ evocation based spell I do not know about, there is no reason to use our evocation spells. I would be interested to hear a scenario where someone has found casting ward/expulse/dismiss undead to be highly useful. (for the actual answer to your question, see Gorthins post)<br>&nbsp;<br>Nazragul Xarn, 40th Season Knight of the Dismal Rage<br>Morell-Thule</td></tr>
