	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You get the spell at 22.&nbsp;&nbsp;(22+1)*5=115.  So you need a skill of 115, AND an int of 75 to get a 75% chance of a successful cast.  This information is from how pure casters and their skills work.<br><br>If you have a higher int than the 75 "base", your success chances will be higher.  For example, my SK just hit 17, so while waiting on the boat to train parry, I decided to work on abjuration.  Since we get endure cold at 15, (15+1)*5=80 is what I should need to get that 75% chance.  However, my SK has a 115 int, so at about skill 50 is when I noticed a lot more successful casts.  At skill 70, I almost never miss.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Chugrahk<br>17 SK BB<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
